Background QikBit is a start-up company producing low cost fitness trackers. Their flagship product, the KwikBit Unit1 (spot the mistake on the patent form) reproduces the functionality of the best-in-class commercial fitness trackers, but is cheap to make. They are currently preparing to pitch to a potential investor and require a selection of charts to include in their presentation and promotional materials.

Q1. Take the data in the dataset qb_revenue_breakdown and make a stacked bar chart showing the sources of revenue across the two years in the dataset.

Question 2. Make a line chart showing monthly sales of the flagship product - the KwikBit Unit 1 - over the last year. This data is inside qb_monthly_sales, but you will need to use filter() or subset() (base R).

Question 3. Make a line chart showing monthly revenue and costs over the last year. This data is also in qb_monthly_sales.

Question 4. Show annual sales of personal fitness trackers over the last 5 years broken down by company as a ribbon plot (use geom_area). This data is in qb_competitors.

```r
qb_competitors %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_area(aes(x = Year, y = Revenue, fill = Company))


<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-chunk-end -->


<!-- rnb-text-begin -->


Question 5.
Now show the sales from the four competitors as a line graph. Include an extra layer that shows the data points used to make the lines.

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxucWJfY29tcGV0aXRvcnMgJT4lXG4gIGdncGxvdCgpICtcbiAgZ2VvbV9saW5lKGFlcyh4ID0gWWVhciwgeSA9IFJldmVudWUsIGNvbG91ciA9IENvbXBhbnkpKSArXG4gIGdlb21fcG9pbnQoYWVzKHggPSBZZWFyLCB5ID0gUmV2ZW51ZSkpXG5cbmBgYFxuYGBgIn0= -->

```r
```r
qb_competitors %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_line(aes(x = Year, y = Revenue, colour = Company)) +
  geom_point(aes(x = Year, y = Revenue))

```r
theme_qb <- 
  theme(
    text = element_text(size = 12),
    title = element_text(size = 14),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 10),
    panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white"),
    panel.grid = element_line(colour = "grey90", linetype = "dashed")
  )
col_scheme <- c("#E89FE9", "#50434F", "#B6A7B5", "#F9A472", "#BD7040")

# It is NOT possible to set the colour scheme in the theme


ggplot(qb_revenue_breakdown) +
  aes(x = Year, y = Revenue, fill = Product) +
  geom_col() +
  scale_fill_manual(values = col_scheme) +
  ggtitle(
    "Breakdown of QikBit Revenue by Product Line",
    subtitle =  "2018 and 2019"
  ) +
  theme_qb

#this answer uses the theme and colour scheme
ggplot(qb_revenue_breakdown) +
  aes(x = Year, y = Revenue, fill = Product) +
  geom_col() +
  scale_fill_manual(values = col_scheme) +
  ggtitle(
    "Breakdown of QikBit Revenue by Product Line",
    subtitle =  "2018 and 2019"
  ) +
  theme_qb

Changing the scales and coordinates when appropriate.

Applying a unified theme, which is described below: Graphs should have white backgrounds, and use colour sparingly. There should be faint grid lines. Font sizes should be ~12pt although titles should be slightly larger and axis labels can be slightly smaller. All plots should use colours from the following company colour scheme. col_scheme <- c(#E89FE9, #50434F, #B6A7B5, #F9A472, #BD7040)

```r
col_scheme <- c(\#E89FE9\, \#50434F\, \#B6A7B5\, \#F9A472\, \#BD7040\)
theme(panel.background = element_rect(fill = \white\, colour = NA))
theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = \light grey\)) +
theme(panel.grid.minor = element_line(colour = \light grey\, size = 0.25))

# Q1. 
qb_revenue_breakdown %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Year, y = Revenue, fill = Product)) +
  geom_bar(stat = \identity\, width =.4) +
  scale_fill_manual(
    values = c(\Accessories\ = \#E89FE9\,
                \Smart Watches\ = \#50434F\,
                \Subscription Services\ = \#B6A7B5\,
                \Trackers\ = \#F9A472\))
  labs(y = \Sources of revenue\) +
  theme(panel.background = element_rect(fill = \white\, colour = NA)) +
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = \light grey\)) +
  theme(panel.grid.minor = element_line(colour = \light grey\, size = 0.25)) +
  theme(axis.title = element_text(size = rel(1.0))) +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_text(size = rel(0.7))) +
  theme(axis.title.y = element_text(size = rel(0.7)))
  
#Q2
qb_monthly_sales %>%
  filter(Cashflow == \Kwikbit Unit 1 Sales\) %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_line(aes(x = Date, y = Amount, colour = Cashflow), colour = \#E89FE9\) +
  ylim(300, 700)+
  labs(x = \Year\, y = \Monthly revenue of Kwikbit Unit 1\) +
  theme(panel.background = element_rect(fill = \white\, colour = NA)) +
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = \light grey\)) +
  theme(panel.grid.minor = element_line(colour = \light grey\, size = 0.25)) +
  theme(axis.title = element_text(size = rel(1.0))) +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_text(size = rel(0.7))) +
  theme(axis.title.y = element_text(size = rel(0.7)))
